h3cRadius.name: h3cRadius
h3cRadius.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cRadius.description: The A3COM-HUAWEI-RADIUS-MIB contains objects to Manage configuration and Monitor running state for RADIUS feature.

h3cRdInfoTable.name: h3cRdInfoTable
h3cRdInfoTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing RADIUS authentication servers.

h3cRdInfoEntry.name: h3cRdInfoEntry
h3cRdInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdGroupName.name: h3cRdGroupName
h3cRdGroupName.description: The name of the RADIUS authentication group referred to in this table entry.

h3cRdPrimAuthIp.name: h3cRdPrimAuthIp
h3cRdPrimAuthIp.description: The IP address of primary RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdPrimUdpPort.name: h3cRdPrimUdpPort
h3cRdPrimUdpPort.description: The UDP port the client is using to send requests to primary RADIUS authentication server. Default value is 1812.

h3cRdPrimState.name: h3cRdPrimState
h3cRdPrimState.description: The state of the primary RADIUS authentication server. 1 (active) The primary authentication server is in active state. 2 (block) The primary authentication server is in block state.

h3cRdSecAuthIp.name: h3cRdSecAuthIp
h3cRdSecAuthIp.description: The IP address of secondary RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdSecUdpPort.name: h3cRdSecUdpPort
h3cRdSecUdpPort.description: The UDP port the client is using to send requests to secondary RADIUS authentication server. Default value is 1812.

h3cRdSecState.name: h3cRdSecState
h3cRdSecState.description: The state of the secondary RADIUS authentication server. 1 (active) The secondary authentication server is in active state. 2 (block) The secondary authentication server is in block state.

h3cRdKey.name: h3cRdKey
h3cRdKey.description: The secret shared between the RADIUS client and RADIUS authentication server used in encoding and decoding sensitive data. When read, h3cRdKey always returns an Octet String of length zero.

h3cRdRetry.name: h3cRdRetry
h3cRdRetry.description: The number of attempts the client will make when trying to send requests to a server before it will consider the attempt failed. Default value is 3.

h3cRdTimeout.name: h3cRdTimeout
h3cRdTimeout.description: The timeout value the client will use when sending requests to a server. The unit is second. Default value is 3.

h3cRdPrimAuthIpAddrType.name: h3cRdPrimAuthIpAddrType
h3cRdPrimAuthIpAddrType.description: The IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of primary RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdPrimAuthIpAddr.name: h3cRdPrimAuthIpAddr
h3cRdPrimAuthIpAddr.description: The IP address of primary RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdSecAuthIpAddrType.name: h3cRdSecAuthIpAddrType
h3cRdSecAuthIpAddrType.description: The IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of secondary RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdSecAuthIpAddr.name: h3cRdSecAuthIpAddr
h3cRdSecAuthIpAddr.description: The IP address of secondary RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdServerType.name: h3cRdServerType
h3cRdServerType.description: Specify the type of RADIUS server. 1 (standard) - Server based on RFC protocol(s). 2 (iphotel) - Server for IP-Hotel or 201+ system. 3 (portal) - Server for iTellin Portal system. 4 (extended) - Server based on RADIUS extensions. Default type is standard.

h3cRdQuietTime.name: h3cRdQuietTime
h3cRdQuietTime.description: The time for server returning active. The unit is minute. When the value is 0, the server state retains active. Default value is 5.

h3cRdUserNameFormat.name: h3cRdUserNameFormat
h3cRdUserNameFormat.description: Specify the user-name format that is sent to RADIUS server. 1 (withoutdomain) - send the user-name without domain. 2 (withdomain) - send the user-name with domain. 3 (keeporignal) - send the user-name as it is entered. Default format is withdomain.

h3cRdRowStatus.name: h3cRdRowStatus
h3cRdRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which support active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To create a new row, h3cRdGroupName must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the h3cRdGroupName MUST NOT be referred by h3cDomainTable in h3cDomainRadiusGroupName column.

h3cRdSecKey.name: h3cRdSecKey
h3cRdSecKey.description: The secret shared between the RADIUS client and the secondary RADIUS authentication server used in encoding and decoding sensitive data. When read, h3cRdSecKey always returns an Octet String of length zero.

h3cRdPrimVpnName.name: h3cRdPrimVpnName
h3cRdPrimVpnName.description: The human-readable name of the VPN in which the primary RADIUS authentication server is placed.

h3cRdSecVpnName.name: h3cRdSecVpnName
h3cRdSecVpnName.description: The human-readable name of the VPN in which the secondary RADIUS authentication server is placed.

h3cRdAuthNasIpAddrType.name: h3cRdAuthNasIpAddrType
h3cRdAuthNasIpAddrType.description: The type (IPv4 or IPv6) of the source IP used to communicate with RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdAuthNasIpAddr.name: h3cRdAuthNasIpAddr
h3cRdAuthNasIpAddr.description: The source IP address used to communicate with RADIUS authentication server.

h3cRdAccInfoEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a RADIUS accounting server.

h3cRdAccGroupName.description: The name of the RADIUS group referred to in this table entry.

h3cRdPrimAccIpAddrType.description: The IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of primary RADIUS accounting server.

h3cRdPrimAccIpAddr.description: The IP address of primary RADIUS accounting server.

h3cRdPrimAccUdpPort.name: h3cRdPrimAccUdpPort
h3cRdPrimAccUdpPort.description: The UDP port the client is using to send requests to primary RADIUS accounting server. Default value is 1813.

h3cRdPrimAccState.name: h3cRdPrimAccState
h3cRdPrimAccState.description: The state of the primary RADIUS accounting server. 1 (active) The primary accounting server is in active state. 2 (block) The primary accounting server is in block state.

h3cRdSecAccIpAddrType.name: h3cRdSecAccIpAddrType
h3cRdSecAccIpAddrType.description: The IP addresses type (IPv4 or IPv6) of secondary RADIUS accounting server.

h3cRdSecAccIpAddr.name: h3cRdSecAccIpAddr
h3cRdSecAccIpAddr.description: The IP address of secondary RADIUS accounting server.

h3cRdSecAccUdpPort.name: h3cRdSecAccUdpPort
h3cRdSecAccUdpPort.description: The UDP port the client is using to send requests to secondary RADIUS accounting server. Default value is 1813.

h3cRdSecAccState.name: h3cRdSecAccState
h3cRdSecAccState.description: The state of the secondary RADIUS accounting server. 1 (active) The secondary accounting server is in active state. 2 (block) The secondary accounting server is in block state.

h3cRdAccKey.name: h3cRdAccKey
h3cRdAccKey.description: The secret shared between the RADIUS client and RADIUS accounting server used in encoding and decoding sensitive data. When read, h3cRdAccKey always returns an Octet String of length zero.

h3cRdAccRetry.name: h3cRdAccRetry
h3cRdAccRetry.description: The number of attempt the client will make when trying to send requests to a server before it will consider the attempt failed. Default value is 3.

h3cRdAccTimeout.name: h3cRdAccTimeout
h3cRdAccTimeout.description: The timeout value the client will use when sending requests to a server. The unit is second. Default value is 3.

h3cRdAccServerType.name: h3cRdAccServerType
h3cRdAccServerType.description: Specify the type of RADIUS server. 1 (standard) - Server based on RFC protocol(s). 2 (iphotel) - Server for IP-Hotel or 201+ system. 3 (portal) - Server for iTellin Portal system. 4 (extended) - Server based on RADIUS extensions. Default type is standard.

h3cRdAccQuietTime.name: h3cRdAccQuietTime
h3cRdAccQuietTime.description: The time for server returning active. The unit is minute. When the value is 0, the server state retains active. Default value is 5.

h3cRdAccFailureAction.name: h3cRdAccFailureAction
h3cRdAccFailureAction.description: Defines the action that authentication should take if authentication succeeds but the associated accounting start fails. 1 (ignore) - treat as authentication success; ignore accounting start failure. 2 (reject) - treat as authentication failed if corresponding accounting start fails. Default value is 1(reject).

h3cRdAccRealTime.name: h3cRdAccRealTime
h3cRdAccRealTime.description: Interval of realtime-accounting packets. The unit is minute. The time must be a multiple of 3. when the value is 0, the device doesn't send realtime-accounting packet. Default value is 12.

h3cRdAccRealTimeRetry.name: h3cRdAccRealTimeRetry
h3cRdAccRealTimeRetry.description: The number of attempt the client will make when trying to send realtime-accounting packet to accounting server before it will consider the attempt failed. Default value is 5.

h3cRdAccSaveStopPktEnable.name: h3cRdAccSaveStopPktEnable
h3cRdAccSaveStopPktEnable.description: The control of whether save stop-accounting packet in local buffer and resend later when the accounting server doesn't respond. When SaveStopPktEnable is set to false, the value of AccStopRetry will be ignored. Default value is true.

h3cRdAccStopRetry.name: h3cRdAccStopRetry
h3cRdAccStopRetry.description: The number of attempt the client will make when trying to send stop-accounting packet to accounting server. Default value is 500.

h3cRdAccDataFlowUnit.name: h3cRdAccDataFlowUnit
h3cRdAccDataFlowUnit.description: Specify data flow format that is sent to RADIUS server. The value SHOULD be set the same as the value of corresponding server. 1 (byte) - Specify 'byte' as the unit of data flow. 2 (kiloByte) - Specify 'kilo-byte' as the unit of data flow. 3 (megaByte) - Specify 'mega-byte' as the unit of data flow. 4 (gigaByte) - Specify 'giga-byte' as the unit of data flow. Default value is 1.

h3cRdAccPacketUnit.name: h3cRdAccPacketUnit
h3cRdAccPacketUnit.description: Specify packet format that is sent to RADIUS server. The value SHOULD be set the same as the value of corresponding server. 1 (onePacket) - Specify 'one-packet' as the unit of packet. 2 (kiloPacket) - Specify 'kilo-packet' as the unit of packet. 3 (megaPacket) - Specify 'mega-packet' as the unit of packet. 4 (gigaPacket) - Specify 'giga-packet' as the unit of packet. Default value is 1.

h3cRdAccRowStatus.name: h3cRdAccRowStatus
h3cRdAccRowStatus.description: This object is responsible for managing the creation, deletion and modification of rows, which support active status and CreateAndGo, Destroy operation. To create a new row, h3cRdAccGroupName must be specified. To destroy an existent row, the h3cRdAccGroupName MUST NOT be referred by h3cDomainTable in h3cDomainRadiusGroupName column.

h3cRdAcctOnEnable.name: h3cRdAcctOnEnable
h3cRdAcctOnEnable.description: The control of Accounting-On function. The Accounting-On function is used by the client to mark the start of accounting (for example, upon booting) by sending Accounting-On packets and to mark the end of accounting (for example, just before a scheduled reboot) by sending Accounting-Off packets. Default value is false.

h3cRdAcctOnSendTimes.name: h3cRdAcctOnSendTimes
h3cRdAcctOnSendTimes.description: The number of Accounting-On packets the client will send before it considers the accounting server failed. Default value is 15.

h3cRdAcctOnSendInterval.name: h3cRdAcctOnSendInterval
h3cRdAcctOnSendInterval.description: Interval of Accounting-On packets. The unit is second. Default value is 3.

h3cRdSecAccKey.name: h3cRdSecAccKey
h3cRdSecAccKey.description: The secret shared between the RADIUS client and the secondary RADIUS accounting server used in encoding and decoding sensitive data. When read, h3cRdSecAccKey always returns an Octet String of length zero.

h3cRdAccNasIpAddrType.name: h3cRdAccNasIpAddrType
h3cRdAccNasIpAddrType.description: The type (IPv4 or IPv6) of the source IP used to communicate with RADIUS accounting server.

h3cRdAccNasIpAddr.name: h3cRdAccNasIpAddr
h3cRdAccNasIpAddr.description: The source IP address used to communicate with RADIUS accounting server.

h3cRadiusAuthErrThreshold.name: h3cRadiusAuthErrThreshold
h3cRadiusAuthErrThreshold.description: The threshold of authentication failure trap. A trap will be sent when the percent of the unsuccessful authentication exceeds this threshold.
